Product Description:
Designed by John Browning himself, the Auto-5 was the first successful semi-automatic shotgun ever produced. The A-5 features a distinctive high rear-end, earning it the nickname "Humpback." The top of the action goes straight back on a level with the barrel before cutting down sharply towards the buttstock. The A-5's unique adjustable friction ring set helps control the amount of recoil. The Final Tribute represents the end of the Auto-5 as a production gun. Browning holding the A-5, and a group of 4 men outside the J.M. Browning & Bro. store, with additional gold markings. title: For Sale/Trade:  VERY NICE 22LR Upper for an AR-15 *Price Reduced*
postcontent:
This upper is a tack driver. The barrel is a dedicated 16" 22 LR (WASP) barrel by CMMG with a 1:16 twist, the action and collar are all stainless steel (the nicest action sold by CMMG), charging hande is made by CMMG for dedicated 22 uppers. It has the regular m4 sight base, a magpul moe carbine handguard, and an A2 flash hider (which can be unscrewed by hand to attach your suppressor should you have one. The upper receiver is a Tactical Innovations AR-15 receiver. And comes with 2 - 25 round magazines.

This is a cream-of-the-crop build, it is nothing like these cheesy, toy-like dedicated 22 AR's that S&W and Mossberg are putting out, this upper has the look and feel of a real 5.56 upper, it is sturdy, feels great, looks great, shoots fantastic (both accurate and reliable - still yet to jam in the first 300 rounds with the cheap Federal Value pack ammo), yet still in a lightweight package.

This upper is a fantastic training tool for your AR (you can practice at 3-4 cents a round, compared to 25-50 cents a round for 223/556, this adds up very quickly! You could dump a mag of 22 for the cost of a couple rounds of 223!). It is accurate enough to be a hunting rifle. Install on your AR lower takes maybe 10 seconds. Spare mags can be purchased for $20.

I have exactly $632.31 into this upper, not including the rear sight (Rock River Arms Dominator [$150] and sightmark red dot [$75] which are not included in the $550 price. I am not looking to make any money on this upper, I am just wanting to start another project. If you want the rear sights (which are Co-Witness) I would do a package deal at $700.

title: For Sale:  Schmidt-Rubin 1911 Rifle 7.5 Swiss, *Very Accurate Rifle*
postcontent:
This is a Schmidt-Rubin 1911 Rifle. It is very similar to the K-31. This rifle has a gorgeous Walnut stock and a bright shiny bore. It is a very accurate rifle. It has been cut down a couple inches and re-crowned (long before it came to me.) It may have been one of the military conversions when they changed the rifles to carbines. This is a very accurate rifle. 

Like all of the rifles in the Schmidt-Rubin family, it is a straight pull design and demonstrates the exceptional quality the Swiss are famous for. 

These rifles are known for being very accurate, ammo is readily available online at a reasonable price and, unlike most military surplus rifles, it is non corrosive which is why the Swiss Rifles look so good after all these years.

This rifle was built in the WW1/WW2 timeframe. There is an interesting piece of history around these rifles. The Swiss managed to stay neutral by being militarily well prepared (and playing both side.) The swiss were such good marksmen that one time a visiting German general came for a Diplomatic visit and a Swiss commander bragged that he could mobilize 1million men at a monets notice. The German responded by asking what he would do if Switzerland was invaded by 3million men. The Swiss commander said, each of my men will take 3 shots and go home.
